hanging from an English rope.

480
00:26:51,569 --> 00:26:52,778
Your servant, sir.

481
00:26:56,282 --> 00:27:00,578
Judge Wilson, forgive me,
but how can anyone see you

482
00:27:00,661 --> 00:27:04,624
if you insist on standing
in Mr. Dickinson's shadow?

483
00:27:05,833 --> 00:27:09,795
James Wilson, also of Pennsylvania.

484
00:27:09,879 --> 00:27:10,963
Sir.

485
00:27:12,340 --> 00:27:13,841
An honor, sir.

486
00:27:14,675 --> 00:27:16,802
Good morning. Good morning.

487
00:27:19,555 --> 00:27:21,682
Good morning, ladies. Good morning.

488
00:27:21,766 --> 00:27:23,309
Steady, steady.

489
00:27:24,936 --> 00:27:27,647
Make gangway, sir. Make gangway!

490
00:27:27,730 --> 00:27:29,982
Good morning, Mr. Wilson. Good morning.

491
00:27:30,066 --> 00:27:33,069
Watch where you're going, damn it.
Over there.

492
00:27:33,444 --> 00:27:36,405
Mcnair, get me out of this thing.

493
00:27:36,489 --> 00:27:38,616
Watch out for my foot.

494
00:27:38,699 --> 00:27:39,825
Good morning, all.

495
00:27:39,909 --> 00:27:41,869
- Morning, Ben.
- Morning, Ben.

496
00:27:42,203 --> 00:27:45,540
Here you are. Two coppers apiece.
Now, straight back to jail with you.

497
00:27:45,623 --> 00:27:48,209
- Good morning, Stephen.
- All right, Benjamin.

498
00:27:49,293 --> 00:27:50,545
Dear god.

499
00:27:53,256 --> 00:27:54,632
What are you staring at?

500
00:27:54,715 --> 00:27:56,926
Haven't you ever seen a great man before?

501
00:27:57,009 --> 00:27:59,303
Good lord, sir.
Do you have the honor to be Dr. Franklin?

502
00:27:59,387 --> 00:28:03,349
Yes, I have that honor. Unfortunately,
the gout accompanies the honor.

503
00:28:03,432 --> 00:28:04,952
Been living too high again, eh, pappy?

504
00:28:05,017 --> 00:28:08,938
Stephen, I only wish king George
felt like my big toe all over.

505
00:28:10,731 --> 00:28:14,485
Mcnair! Fetch a pillow and two more rums.

506
00:28:14,569 --> 00:28:16,004
Well, Franklin, where's that idiot Lee?

507
00:28:16,028 --> 00:28:17,655
Is he back yet? I don't see him.

508
00:28:17,738 --> 00:28:20,491
Softly, John. Your voice
is hurting my foot.

509
00:28:20,575 --> 00:28:24,161
One more Clay, Franklin. That's how long
I'll remain silent, not a minute longer.

510
00:28:24,245 --> 00:28:26,789
That strutting popinjay
was so damn sure of himself.

511
00:28:26,872 --> 00:28:29,083
He's had time to bring back
a dozen proposals by now.

512
00:28:29,166 --> 00:28:30,209
Tell me, James.

513
00:28:30,293 --> 00:28:33,629
How do you explain the strange,
monumental quietude

514
00:28:33,713 --> 00:28:36,215
that congress has been treated
to these past 30 days?

515
00:28:36,299 --> 00:28:39,927
Has the ill wind
of independence finally blown itself out?

516
00:28:40,803 --> 00:28:42,638
Well, if you ask me...

517
00:28:42,722 --> 00:28:46,392
For myself, I must confess
that a month free from new england noise

518
00:28:46,475 --> 00:28:48,436
is more therapeutic
than a month in the country.

519
00:28:48,519 --> 00:28:50,146
Don't you agree, James?

520
00:28:50,229 --> 00:28:51,355
Well, lfeel...

521
00:28:51,439 --> 00:28:53,482
Mr. Adams, pray look for your voice, sir.

522
00:28:53,566 --> 00:28:58,237
It cannot be far, and god knows we need
the entertainment in congress.

523
00:29:02,450 --> 00:29:03,659
Congratulations, John.

524
00:29:03,743 --> 00:29:05,762
You just made
your greatest contribution to independence.

525
00:29:05,786 --> 00:29:07,079
You kept your flap shut.

526
00:29:07,163 --> 00:29:08,581
One more day, Franklin.

527
00:29:08,664 --> 00:29:10,916
Then I shall do the proposing.

528
00:29:12,251 --> 00:29:15,963
Gentlemen, the usual morning
festivities concluded,

529
00:29:16,047 --> 00:29:18,466
I will now call congress to order.

530
00:29:18,883 --> 00:29:20,384
Mr. thomson.

531
00:29:23,971 --> 00:29:27,600
The second continental congress meeting in
the city of Philadelphia is now in session.

532
00:29:27,683 --> 00:29:31,228
7 June, 1776, the 380th meeting.

533
00:29:31,312 --> 00:29:32,938
Sweet Jesus!

534
00:29:34,774 --> 00:29:38,110
The honorable John hancock
of Massachusetts bay, president.

535
00:29:40,154 --> 00:29:43,032
Thank you, Mr. thomson. Mr. mcnair.

536
00:29:43,115 --> 00:29:46,452
The stores of rum and other
drinking spirits are hereby closed

537
00:29:46,535 --> 00:29:50,039
to the colony of Rhode Island
for a period of three days.

538
00:29:50,122 --> 00:29:51,499
Yes, sir.

539
00:29:51,582 --> 00:29:53,376
Johnny, you can't do that.

540
00:29:53,459 --> 00:29:56,754
Sit down, Mr. Hopkins.
You've abused the privilege.

541
00:29:59,256 --> 00:30:01,133
The chair would like to
take this opportunity

542
00:30:01,217 --> 00:30:04,178
to welcome Dr. lyman hall of Georgia
to this congress,

543
00:30:04,261 --> 00:30:06,263
and hopes he will make the best of it.

544
00:30:09,475 --> 00:30:11,352
My god, it's hot.

545
00:30:12,353 --> 00:30:14,563
The secretary will read the roll.

546
00:30:14,647 --> 00:30:16,899
All members present
with the following exceptions.

547
00:30:17,441 --> 00:30:20,236
"Mr. paine, Mr. Gerry,
Mr. Samuel Adams of Massachusetts,

548
00:30:20,319 --> 00:30:21,987
"Mr. Morton of Pennsylvania,

549
00:30:22,113 --> 00:30:24,323
"Mr. wythe and
Mr. Richard Henry Lee of Virginia."

550
00:30:24,824 --> 00:30:27,576
And the entire delegation of New Jersey.

551
00:30:27,993 --> 00:30:29,829
I'm concerned over the continual absence

552
00:30:29,912 --> 00:30:33,040
of one-thirteenth of this congress.
Where is New Jersey?

553
00:30:33,457 --> 00:30:36,335
Somewhere between
New York and Pennsylvania.

554
00:30:39,839 --> 00:30:41,590
Thank you very much.

555
00:30:42,341 --> 00:30:46,137
Dr. Franklin, have you heard anything?
Your son resides there.

556
00:30:46,220 --> 00:30:47,471
Son, sir? What son?

557
00:30:48,431 --> 00:30:51,058
The royal governor of New Jersey, sir.

558
00:30:51,767 --> 00:30:53,769
As that title might suggest, sir,

559
00:30:53,853 --> 00:30:56,188
we are not in touch at the present time.

560
00:30:56,605 --> 00:30:58,441
Yes. Well...

561
00:30:59,024 --> 00:31:00,943
Now for the weather report,

562
00:31:01,026 --> 00:31:03,028
Mr. Jefferson of Virginia.

563
00:31:05,322 --> 00:31:06,323
Mr. Jefferson!

564
00:31:07,408 --> 00:31:08,534
Present, sir.

565
00:31:09,076 --> 00:31:10,703
May we hear about the weather?

566
00:31:10,995 --> 00:31:13,581
As if it weren't speaking for itself.

567
00:31:15,207 --> 00:31:17,793
Eighty-seven degrees of temperature,

568
00:31:17,877 --> 00:31:20,880
thirty-point-aught-six inches of Mercury.

569
00:31:21,505 --> 00:31:22,715
Wind...

570
00:31:23,758 --> 00:31:26,093
From the southwest for the rest of the day.

571
00:31:26,177 --> 00:31:27,636
And tonight...

572
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:29,972
Tonight I'm leaving for home.

573
00:31:30,055 --> 00:31:31,515
On business?

574
00:31:31,599 --> 00:31:32,683
Family business.

575
00:31:32,933 --> 00:31:35,519
Give her a flourish for me, young feller.

576
00:32:03,255 --> 00:32:05,883
"From the commander,
army of the united colonies to New York,

577
00:32:05,966 --> 00:32:08,344
"dispatch number 1,137."

578
00:32:08,427 --> 00:32:10,596
Sweet Jesus!

579
00:32:11,096 --> 00:32:12,741
"To the honorable congress,
John hancock, president.

580
00:32:12,765 --> 00:32:16,519
"Dear sir, it is with grave apprehension
that I have learned this day

581
00:32:16,602 --> 00:32:18,729
"of the sailing from halifax, Nova Scotia,

582
00:32:18,813 --> 00:32:22,233
"of a considerable force of British troops
in the company of foreign mercenaries

583
00:32:22,316 --> 00:32:24,902
"and under the command
of general sir William howe."

584
00:32:24,985 --> 00:32:27,446
"There can be no doubt
that their destination is New York,

585
00:32:27,530 --> 00:32:30,699
"for to take and hold this city
and the Hudson valley beyond

586
00:32:30,783 --> 00:32:33,619
"would serve to separate new england
from the rest of the colonies,

587
00:32:33,702 --> 00:32:36,747
"permitting both sections
to be crushed in turn.

588
00:32:36,831 --> 00:32:39,416
"Sadly, I see no way
of stopping them at the present time,

589
00:32:39,500 --> 00:32:41,877
"as my army is absolutely falling apart.

590
00:32:41,961 --> 00:32:43,963
"My military chest is totally exhausted.

591
00:32:44,046 --> 00:32:47,299
"My commissary general
has strained his credit to the last.

592
00:32:47,383 --> 00:32:50,970
"My quartermaster has no food,
no arms, no ammunition,

593
00:32:51,095 --> 00:32:54,014
"and my troops are in a
state of near mutiny.

594
00:32:54,098 --> 00:32:58,978
"L pray god some relief arrives
before the armada, but fear it will not.

595
00:32:59,061 --> 00:33:00,604
"Your obedient,

596
00:33:01,981 --> 00:33:03,399
"g. Washington."

597
00:33:04,191 --> 00:33:05,734
Mr. president!

598
00:33:05,818 --> 00:33:06,819
Colonel mckean.

599
00:33:06,902 --> 00:33:09,488
Surely we have managed to promote

600
00:33:09,572 --> 00:33:13,701
the gloomiest man on this continent
to the head of our troops.

601
00:33:13,784 --> 00:33:18,080
Those dispatches
are the most depressing accumulation

602
00:33:18,163 --> 00:33:23,460
of disaster, doom and despair
in the entire annals of military history.

603
00:33:24,169 --> 00:33:26,255
Colonel mckean, please!

604
00:33:26,338 --> 00:33:27,339
What?

605
00:33:28,340 --> 00:33:29,842
It's too hot.

606
00:33:31,051 --> 00:33:32,803
Well, I suppose so.

607
00:33:33,679 --> 00:33:37,892
General Washington will continue
wording his dispatches as he sees fit.

608
00:33:37,975 --> 00:33:39,935
And I'm sure we all pray

609
00:33:40,019 --> 00:33:43,939
he finds happier thoughts
to convey in the near future.

610
00:33:45,274 --> 00:33:47,109
Mr. thomson, are there any resolutions?

611
00:33:47,526 --> 00:33:49,695
Dr. Josiah bartlett of New Hampshire.

612
00:33:50,988 --> 00:33:54,158
"Resolved, that for the duration
of the present hostilities,

613
00:33:54,241 --> 00:33:57,620
"the congress discourage
every type of extravagance and dissipation,

614
00:33:57,703 --> 00:34:00,331
"elaborate funerals
and other expensive diversions,

615
00:34:00,414 --> 00:34:03,334
"especially all horse racing, gambling,

616
00:34:03,417 --> 00:34:06,086
"and other forms of sinful
activity, which..."

617
00:34:06,170 --> 00:34:07,630
Fire wagon!

618
00:34:24,813 --> 00:34:26,398
Where's the fire? Can anybody tell?

619
00:34:26,482 --> 00:34:29,122
- Looks like the Pemberton house.
- It couldn't be. It's brand new.

620
00:34:29,193 --> 00:34:32,571
- It might be the city tavern.
- Bite your tongue, man.

621
00:34:41,914 --> 00:34:43,290
Benjy, I'm back!

622
00:34:43,916 --> 00:34:47,002
- L'm back, Johnny!
- Richard, lad, welcome back.

623
00:34:50,881 --> 00:34:51,882
Lee, is it done?

624
00:34:51,966 --> 00:34:53,759
First things first. Tom!

625
00:34:53,842 --> 00:34:58,222
Tom! Tom, your little bride wants to know,
"when's he coming home?"

626
00:34:58,305 --> 00:34:59,390
I leave tonight.

627
00:34:59,473 --> 00:35:01,016
Never mind that, man. Ls it done?

628
00:35:01,100 --> 00:35:03,268
Done? Why, certain-Lee.

629
00:35:04,103 --> 00:35:07,856
Mr. president, I have returned from
Virginia with the following resolution,

630
00:35:07,940 --> 00:35:11,485
"resolved, that these united colonies are,
and of a right ought to be,

631
00:35:11,568 --> 00:35:13,028
"free and independent states,

632
00:35:13,112 --> 00:35:15,823
"that they are absolved
from allegiance to the British crown,

633
00:35:15,906 --> 00:35:19,284
"and that all political connection between
them and the state of Great Britain is,

634
00:35:19,368 --> 00:35:22,037
"and ought to be, totally dissolved."

635
00:35:22,121 --> 00:35:23,288
Hear, hear!

636
00:35:23,372 --> 00:35:26,166
Mr. president, I second the proposal.

637
00:35:26,250 --> 00:35:28,127
The resolution has been proposed
and seconded.

638
00:35:28,210 --> 00:35:30,754
The chair will now entertain debate.

639
00:35:31,672 --> 00:35:33,298
- Mr. Dickinson.
- Mr. president.

640
00:35:33,590 --> 00:35:35,718
Pennsylvania moves, as always,

641
00:35:35,801 --> 00:35:39,930
that the question
of independence be postponed indefinitely.

642
00:35:40,014 --> 00:35:41,807
I second the motion.

643
00:35:42,266 --> 00:35:43,726
Judge Wilson,

644
00:35:44,309 --> 00:35:47,062
in your eagerness to be loved,
you seem to have forgotten

645
00:35:47,146 --> 00:35:50,107
that Pennsylvania
cannot second its own motion.

646
00:35:51,525 --> 00:35:53,235
Delaware seconds.

647
00:35:53,318 --> 00:35:55,612
You would, you lousy wart.

648
00:35:56,155 --> 00:35:59,324
The motion to postpone
has been moved and seconded.

649
00:35:59,408 --> 00:36:00,826
Mr. thomson.

650
00:36:02,327 --> 00:36:04,121
On the motion to postpone indefinitely

651
00:36:04,204 --> 00:36:07,041
the resolution on independency
or proceed with the debate,

652
00:36:07,124 --> 00:36:08,792
all those in favor of debate say "yea,"

653
00:36:08,876 --> 00:36:10,419
all those for postponement say "nay."

654
00:36:10,502 --> 00:36:11,587
New Hampshire?

655
00:36:12,504 --> 00:36:14,715
New Hampshire favors debate, and says yea.

656
00:36:17,009 --> 00:36:19,178
New Hampshire says yea. Massachusetts?

657
00:36:19,762 --> 00:36:24,266
Massachusetts, having borne the brunt
of the king's tyranny...

658
00:36:24,349 --> 00:36:26,351
Yes, I said tyranny!

659
00:36:27,102 --> 00:36:30,105
Massachusetts now,
and for all time, says yea.

660
00:36:31,690 --> 00:36:33,525
Massachusetts says yea.

661
00:36:33,859 --> 00:36:35,360
Rhode Island?

662
00:36:36,361 --> 00:36:37,780
Mr. Hopkins?

663
00:36:38,530 --> 00:36:39,907
Where's Rhode Island?

664
00:36:39,990 --> 00:36:42,951
Rhode Island is out visiting the necessary.

665
00:36:43,243 --> 00:36:46,580
After what Rhode Island's consumed,
i can't say I'm surprised.

666
00:36:46,663 --> 00:36:48,582
We'll come back to him, Mr. thomson.

667
00:36:48,665 --> 00:36:50,417
Rhode Island passes.

668
00:36:55,172 --> 00:36:56,298
Connecticut?

669
00:36:58,383 --> 00:37:00,969
While Connecticut has, till now,

670
00:37:01,053 --> 00:37:03,305
been against this proposal,

671
00:37:03,889 --> 00:37:06,350
our legislature
has instructed me that in the event

672
00:37:06,433 --> 00:37:09,645
it is introduced by any colony
outside of new england,

673
00:37:09,728 --> 00:37:13,107
we could not any longer
withhold our support. Connecticut says yea.

674
00:37:13,190 --> 00:37:14,316
Hear! Hear!

675
00:37:14,399 --> 00:37:16,735
Connecticut says yea. New York?

676
00:37:18,237 --> 00:37:20,656
New York abstains courteously.

677
00:37:20,906 --> 00:37:22,407
New York abstains.

678
00:37:22,491 --> 00:37:23,534
Courteously.

679
00:37:25,744 --> 00:37:26,829
New Jersey?

680
00:37:26,912 --> 00:37:28,330
Absent, Mr. secretary.

681
00:37:30,415 --> 00:37:32,292
New Jersey's absent. Pennsylvania?

682
00:37:33,085 --> 00:37:36,630
Pennsylvania, for the 24th time, says nay.

683
00:37:36,713 --> 00:37:38,882
Pennsylvania says nay. Delaware?

684
00:37:39,925 --> 00:37:44,680
Delaware, as ever for independence,
says yea.

685
00:37:44,763 --> 00:37:47,182
Delaware says yea. Maryland?

686
00:37:48,100 --> 00:37:51,478
Maryland would welcome independence
if it were given,

687
00:37:51,562 --> 00:37:54,773
but is highly skeptical
that it can be taken.

688
00:37:54,857 --> 00:37:56,525
Maryland says nay.

689
00:37:58,318 --> 00:38:00,529
Maryland says nay. Virginia?

690
00:38:00,612 --> 00:38:03,365
Virginia, the first colony, says yea!

691
00:38:06,702 --> 00:38:09,037
Virginia says yea. North Carolina?

692
00:38:09,121 --> 00:38:13,417
North Carolina
respectfully yields to south Carolina.

693
00:38:13,500 --> 00:38:14,543
South Carolina?

694
00:38:14,626 --> 00:38:16,128
Mr. president,

695
00:38:16,712 --> 00:38:20,257
although we of south Carolina
have never seriously considered

696
00:38:20,340 --> 00:38:22,551
the question of independence,

697
00:38:22,634 --> 00:38:26,471
when a gentleman proposes it,
attention must be paid.

698
00:38:28,098 --> 00:38:31,685
However, we in the deep south,

699
00:38:31,768 --> 00:38:33,729
unlike our friends in new england,

700
00:38:33,812 --> 00:38:37,441
have no cause for impatience
at the present time.

701
00:38:38,567 --> 00:38:41,904
If at some future date it becomes the
wish of all our sister colonies,

702
00:38:41,987 --> 00:38:45,908
to effect a separation,
we will not stand in the way.

703
00:38:45,991 --> 00:38:47,826
But for the time being,

704
00:38:47,910 --> 00:38:51,121
south Carolina will wait and watch.

705
00:38:52,122 --> 00:38:53,707
The vote is nay.

706
00:38:56,001 --> 00:38:57,044
North Carolina...

707
00:38:57,127 --> 00:38:59,463
Says nay. Yes, Mr. Hewes. I know.

708
00:39:02,090 --> 00:39:03,133
Georgia.

709
00:39:06,553 --> 00:39:07,804
Georgia.

710
00:39:09,389 --> 00:39:14,269
Mr. president, Georgia seems to be split
right down the middle on this issue.

711
00:39:14,353 --> 00:39:17,189
The people are against it, and I'm for it.

712
00:39:19,650 --> 00:39:22,903
However, I'm afraid I'm not quite certain

713
00:39:22,986 --> 00:39:27,115
whether representing the people means
relying on theirjudgment or on my own.

714
00:39:27,199 --> 00:39:31,912
In all fairness, until I can figure that
out, I'd better lean a little on their side.

715
00:39:31,995 --> 00:39:33,205
Georgia says nay.

716
00:39:37,876 --> 00:39:39,962
Georgia says nay.

717
00:39:40,045 --> 00:39:41,588
Rhode Island?

718
00:39:43,507 --> 00:39:45,926
Second call, Rhode Island!

719
00:39:46,551 --> 00:39:48,262
Rhode Island!

720
00:39:48,512 --> 00:39:50,973
I'm coming! I'm coming!

721
00:39:51,223 --> 00:39:53,350
Hold your damn horses.

722
00:39:53,433 --> 00:39:56,937
- We're waiting on you, Mr. Hopkins.
- Well, it won't kill you.

723
00:39:57,020 --> 00:40:00,482
You'd think the congress
would have its own privy.

724
00:40:00,565 --> 00:40:02,609
All right, where does she stand?

725
00:40:02,693 --> 00:40:06,530
Five for debate, five for postponement,
one abstention and one absence.

726
00:40:06,613 --> 00:40:08,407
So it's up to me, huh?

727
00:40:08,490 --> 00:40:10,534
Well, I'll tell you.

728
00:40:10,617 --> 00:40:15,080
In all my years,
i never seen, heard nor smelled an issue

729
00:40:15,163 --> 00:40:18,000
that was so dangerous
it couldn't be talked about.

730
00:40:18,083 --> 00:40:21,837
Hell, yes! I'm for debating anything.
Rhode Island says yea.

731
00:40:24,673 --> 00:40:27,926
- Mcnair, get Mr. Hopkins a rum.
- But you said...

732
00:40:28,010 --> 00:40:30,679
Get him the whole damn barrel if he wants.

733
00:40:31,638 --> 00:40:34,057
The chair now declares this congress
a committee of the whole

734
00:40:34,141 --> 00:40:37,561
for the purpose of debating
Virginia's resolution on independence.

735
00:40:37,644 --> 00:40:39,146
Mr. Dickinson.

736
00:40:41,023 --> 00:40:45,986
Well, now,
you've got your way at last, Mr. Adams.

737
00:40:46,361 --> 00:40:48,697
The matter may now be discussed.

738
00:40:49,531 --> 00:40:51,992
I confess I'm almost relieved.

739
00:40:52,659 --> 00:40:56,163
There's a question
I've been fairly itching to ask you.

740
00:40:58,540 --> 00:40:59,624
Why?

741
00:40:59,708 --> 00:41:01,918
Why what, Mr. Dickinson?

742
00:41:02,002 --> 00:41:04,671
Well, why independence, Mr. Adams?

743
00:41:05,172 --> 00:41:08,091
Well, for the obvious reason
that our continued association

744
00:41:08,175 --> 00:41:11,053
with Great Britain has grown intolerable.

745
00:41:11,136 --> 00:41:13,680
Well, to whom, Mr. Adams? To you?

746
00:41:14,639 --> 00:41:17,601
Well, then I suggest
you sever your ties immediately.

747
00:41:17,684 --> 00:41:22,898
But please be kind enough
to leave the rest of us where we are.

748
00:41:23,690 --> 00:41:25,692
For myself, I have no objection at all

749
00:41:25,776 --> 00:41:28,487
to being part of the greatest
empire on earth,

750
00:41:28,570 --> 00:41:31,531
to enjoying its protection
and sharing its benefits.

751
00:41:31,615 --> 00:41:32,866
Benefits?

752
00:41:34,076 --> 00:41:35,535
What benefits?

753
00:41:36,203 --> 00:41:39,414
Crippling taxes? Cruel repressions?

754
00:41:39,498 --> 00:41:41,124
Abolished rights?

755
00:41:42,876 --> 00:41:46,797
Is that all england means to you, sir?

756
00:41:48,924 --> 00:41:52,135
Is that all
the pride and affection you can muster

757
00:41:52,219 --> 00:41:54,638
for the nation that bore you?

758
00:41:54,721 --> 00:41:58,475
For the noblest, most civilized nation
on the face of this planet?

759
00:41:58,558 --> 00:42:02,187
Well, would you have us forsake
Hastings and magna carta,

760
00:42:02,270 --> 00:42:05,857
strongbow and lionheart,
Drake and marlborough,

761
00:42:05,941 --> 00:42:07,943
tudors, Stuarts and plantagenets?

762
00:42:08,026 --> 00:42:09,653
For what, sir?

763
00:42:09,736 --> 00:42:11,738
Well, tell me. For what?

764
00:42:14,991 --> 00:42:16,243
For you?

765
00:42:19,746 --> 00:42:23,875
Some men are patriots,
like general Washington,

766
00:42:23,959 --> 00:42:26,169
and some are anarchists, like Mr. paine.

767
00:42:26,253 --> 00:42:29,005
Some even are internationalists,
like Dr. Franklin.

768
00:42:29,089 --> 00:42:31,633
But you, sir...

769
00:42:33,260 --> 00:42:36,012
You are merely an agitator,

770
00:42:36,096 --> 00:42:37,514
disturbing the peace,

771
00:42:37,597 --> 00:42:40,058
creating disorder,
endangering the public welfare.

772
00:42:40,142 --> 00:42:41,518
And for what?

773
00:42:41,601 --> 00:42:43,895
Your petty little personal complaints.

774
00:42:43,979 --> 00:42:46,022
Your taxes are too high.

775
00:42:47,649 --> 00:42:51,403
Well, sir, so are mine.

776
00:42:54,239 --> 00:42:56,449
Come, come, Mr. Adams.

777
00:42:57,075 --> 00:43:00,453
If you have grievances,
and I'm sure you have,

778
00:43:00,537 --> 00:43:04,040
our present system must provide
a gentler means of redressing them

779
00:43:04,124 --> 00:43:06,126
short of revolution.

780
00:43:07,043 --> 00:43:09,212
Yes, that's what he wants.

781
00:43:09,296 --> 00:43:11,214
Nothing less will satisfy him.

782
00:43:11,298 --> 00:43:14,092
Violence, rebellion, treason.

783
00:43:16,595 --> 00:43:18,638
Now, Mr. Adams,

784
00:43:19,806 --> 00:43:22,976
are these the acts of englishmen?

785
00:43:23,059 --> 00:43:25,604
Not englishmen, Dickinson. Americans.

786
00:43:25,687 --> 00:43:27,647
No, sir. Englishmen!

787
00:43:28,440 --> 00:43:30,400
Please, Mr. Dickinson,
must you start banging?

788
00:43:30,483 --> 00:43:31,735
How is a man to sleep?

789
00:43:33,320 --> 00:43:36,781
Forgive me, Dr. Franklin,
but must you start speaking?

790
00:43:36,865 --> 00:43:38,992
How is a man to stay awake?

791
00:43:40,493 --> 00:43:42,579
We'll promise to be quiet, sir.

792
00:43:42,662 --> 00:43:45,874
I'm sure everyone prefers
that you remain asleep.

793
00:43:46,208 --> 00:43:48,293
If I'm to hear myself
called an englishman, sir,

794
00:43:48,376 --> 00:43:50,378
I assure you I prefer I'd remained asleep.

795
00:43:51,671 --> 00:43:54,257
Now, what's so terrible
about being called an englishman?

796
00:43:54,341 --> 00:43:55,884
The English don't seem to mind.

797
00:43:56,218 --> 00:43:59,596
Nor would I, were I given the
full rights of an englishman.

798
00:43:59,679 --> 00:44:03,642
But to call me one without those rights
is like calling an ox a bull.

799
00:44:03,725 --> 00:44:07,270
He's thankful for the honor, but he'd much
rather have restored what's rightfully his.

800
00:44:13,902 --> 00:44:16,696
When did you first notice
they were missing, sir?

801
00:44:22,369 --> 00:44:25,205
Fortunately, the people of these colonies

802
00:44:25,288 --> 00:44:27,916
maintain a higher regard
for their mother country.

803
00:44:28,875 --> 00:44:31,795
Higher, certainly, than she feels for them.

804
00:44:31,878 --> 00:44:36,091
Never was such a valuable possession
so stupidly and so recklessly managed

805
00:44:36,174 --> 00:44:39,094
than this entire continent
by the British crown.

806
00:44:39,177 --> 00:44:42,347
Our industry discouraged,
our resources pillaged.

807
00:44:43,598 --> 00:44:46,393
Worst of all, our very character stifled.

808
00:44:47,060 --> 00:44:49,312
We've spawned a new race here,
Mr. Dickinson.

809
00:44:49,396 --> 00:44:50,730
Rougher, simpler,

810
00:44:50,814 --> 00:44:53,441
more violent, more enterprising,

811
00:44:53,525 --> 00:44:54,985
less refined.

812
00:44:55,610 --> 00:44:57,362
We're a new nationality.

813
00:44:57,445 --> 00:44:59,572
We require a new nation.

814
00:45:02,867 --> 00:45:03,952
Well,

815
00:45:04,744 --> 00:45:07,205
that may be your opinion, Dr. Franklin,

816
00:45:07,289 --> 00:45:12,752
but, as I said,
the people feel quite differently.

817
00:45:12,836 --> 00:45:16,214
Now, what do you know
about the people, Dickinson?

818
00:45:16,298 --> 00:45:19,884
You don't speak for the people.
You represent only yourself.

819
00:45:19,968 --> 00:45:22,053
And that precious status quo

820
00:45:22,137 --> 00:45:25,515
you keep imploring the people
to preserve for their own good

821
00:45:25,598 --> 00:45:29,728
is nothing more than the eternal
preservation of your own property.

822
00:45:31,271 --> 00:45:34,024
Mr. Adams, you have an annoying talent

823
00:45:34,107 --> 00:45:36,192
for making such delightful words

824
00:45:36,276 --> 00:45:39,487
as "property" sound quite distasteful.

825
00:45:39,571 --> 00:45:42,490
In heaven's name,
what's wrong with property?

826
00:45:43,199 --> 00:45:46,328
Perhaps you've forgotten
that many of us first came to these shores

827
00:45:46,411 --> 00:45:49,039
in order to secure rights to property,

828
00:45:49,122 --> 00:45:53,376
and that we hold these rights
no less dear than the rights you speak of.

829
00:45:53,460 --> 00:45:57,922
Yes. So safe, so fat,
so comfortable in Pennsylvania.

830
00:45:58,006 --> 00:46:00,383
And what is this independence of yours

831
00:46:00,467 --> 00:46:03,178
except the private grievance
of Massachusetts?

832
00:46:03,261 --> 00:46:05,972
Why is it always Boston
that breaks the king's peace?

833
00:46:06,056 --> 00:46:10,435
My dear congress,
you must not adopt this evil measure.

834
00:46:10,518 --> 00:46:12,729
It is the work of the devil.

835
00:46:12,812 --> 00:46:15,148
Leave it where it belongs.

836
00:46:15,982 --> 00:46:17,400
In new england.

837
00:46:17,484 --> 00:46:21,154
Brother Dickinson, new england has been
fighting the devil for more than 100 years.

838
00:46:21,696 --> 00:46:26,409
And as of now, brother sherman,
the devil has been winning hands down.

839
00:46:27,077 --> 00:46:30,413
Why, at this very moment,
he's sitting right here in this congress.

840
00:46:30,497 --> 00:46:34,334
Don't let him deceive you.
This proposal is entirely his doing.

841
00:46:34,417 --> 00:46:36,086
It may bear Virginia's name,

842
00:46:36,169 --> 00:46:40,090
but it reeks of Adams,
Adams and more Adams.

843
00:46:40,173 --> 00:46:45,470
Look at him. Ready to lead this continent
down the fiery path of total destruction.

844
00:46:45,553 --> 00:46:49,682
Good god! Why can't you acknowledge
what already exists?

845
00:46:49,766 --> 00:46:53,269
It has been more than a year
since Concord and Lexington.

846
00:46:53,353 --> 00:46:55,647
Damn it, man, we're at war, right now!

847
00:46:55,730 --> 00:46:58,983
You may be at war.
You, Boston and John Adams.

848
00:46:59,067 --> 00:47:01,694
But you will never speak for Pennsylvania.

849
00:47:01,778 --> 00:47:02,821
Nor for Delaware.

850
00:47:02,904 --> 00:47:07,283
Mr. read, you represent
only one-third of Delaware.

851
00:47:07,367 --> 00:47:09,452
The sensible third, Mr. Rodney.

852
00:47:09,536 --> 00:47:12,705
Sit down, you scurvy dog,
or I'll knock you down.

853
00:47:13,540 --> 00:47:14,958
Sit down, all three of you!

854
00:47:15,041 --> 00:47:17,043
Mcnair, do something about that damn dog!

855
00:47:17,127 --> 00:47:18,628
And here, fetch me a rum.

856
00:47:18,711 --> 00:47:20,797
- Get that dog first!
- Rum, rum!

857
00:47:20,880 --> 00:47:22,674
I only got two hands.

858
00:47:27,512 --> 00:47:29,222
Christ, it's hot!

859
00:47:41,609 --> 00:47:43,653
Please do go on, gentlemen.

860
00:47:43,736 --> 00:47:46,030
You're making the only breeze
in Philadelphia.

861
00:47:47,782 --> 00:47:49,117
Mr. Adams,

862
00:47:49,784 --> 00:47:52,704
perhaps you could
clear up something for me?

863
00:47:53,371 --> 00:47:55,498
After we have achieved independence,

864
00:47:55,582 --> 00:47:58,251
who do you propose
would govern in south Carolina?

865
00:48:00,044 --> 00:48:01,588
The people, of course.

866
00:48:02,130 --> 00:48:04,966
Which people, sir?
The people of south Carolina

867
00:48:05,091 --> 00:48:07,385
or the people of Massachusetts?

868
00:48:07,719 --> 00:48:09,220
Why don't you admit it, neddy?

869
00:48:09,304 --> 00:48:12,223
You're against independence now
and you always will be.

870
00:48:12,307 --> 00:48:13,600
Aye.

871
00:48:15,727 --> 00:48:19,314
Gentlemen, you refuse to understand us.

872
00:48:19,397 --> 00:48:22,150
We desire independence. Yes.

873
00:48:23,109 --> 00:48:25,820
For south Carolina. That is our country.

874
00:48:27,113 --> 00:48:30,200
And as such,
we don't wish to belong to anyone.

875
00:48:30,283 --> 00:48:32,952
Not to england and not to you.

876
00:48:34,120 --> 00:48:36,748
We intend to have one nation, Rutledge.

877
00:48:36,831 --> 00:48:40,043
A nation of sovereign states, Mr. Adams.

878
00:48:40,126 --> 00:48:45,715
United for our mutual protection,
but separate for our individual pursuits.

879
00:48:45,798 --> 00:48:48,760
Now, that is what
we have understood it to be,

880
00:48:48,843 --> 00:48:51,638
and that is what we will support.

881
00:48:53,139 --> 00:48:55,642
As soon as everyone supports it.

882
00:48:59,646 --> 00:49:01,981
Well, there you are, Mr. Adams.

883
00:49:02,774 --> 00:49:05,068
You must see that we need time.

884
00:49:05,568 --> 00:49:10,615
Time to make certain who we are and where
we stand in regard to one another.

885
00:49:10,698 --> 00:49:14,661
For if we do not determine the nature
of the beast before we set it free,

886
00:49:14,744 --> 00:49:17,413
it will end by consuming us all.

887
00:49:17,497 --> 00:49:19,707
For once in your life, Wilson,

888
00:49:20,667 --> 00:49:22,168
take a chance.

889
00:49:23,795 --> 00:49:25,672
I say the time is now.

890
00:49:26,839 --> 00:49:28,800
It may never come again.

891
00:49:29,551 --> 00:49:33,304
Your clock is fast, Mr. Adams.
I say we're not yet ripe for independence.

892
00:49:33,513 --> 00:49:36,724
Not ripe? Hell, we're
rotting for want of it.

893
00:49:37,308 --> 00:49:41,187
Gentlemen, please,
what in god's name is the infernal hurry?

894
00:49:41,271 --> 00:49:43,273
Why must this question be settled now?

895
00:49:43,356 --> 00:49:45,608
What's wrong with now, Mr. chase?

896
00:49:45,858 --> 00:49:48,069
General Washington is in the field.

897
00:49:48,152 --> 00:49:52,282
If he's defeated, as it now appears,
we'll be inviting the hangman.

898
00:49:52,365 --> 00:49:56,452
But if, by some miracle,
he should actually win,

899
00:49:56,536 --> 00:49:59,247
we can then declare anything
we damn please.

900
00:49:59,330 --> 00:50:02,166
The sentiments of north Carolina precisely.

901
00:50:02,875 --> 00:50:05,003
Has it ever occurred to either of you

902
00:50:05,086 --> 00:50:09,549
that an army needs something
to fight for in order to win?

903
00:50:09,716 --> 00:50:13,136
A purpose? A goal? A flag of its own?

904
00:50:13,595 --> 00:50:14,929
Mr. Adams,

905
00:50:15,847 --> 00:50:21,185
how can a nation of only 2 million souls
stand up to an empire of 10 million?

906
00:50:21,269 --> 00:50:22,687
Think of it. 10 million.

907
00:50:22,770 --> 00:50:25,106
How do we compensate for that shortage?

908
00:50:25,189 --> 00:50:27,900
It's simple, Mr. chase.
Increase and multiply.

909
00:50:27,984 --> 00:50:29,360
How's that?

910
00:50:30,695 --> 00:50:33,489
We will more than compensate with spirit.

911
00:50:33,865 --> 00:50:36,659
I tell you, there is
a spirit out there among the people

912
00:50:36,743 --> 00:50:38,828
that is sadly lacking in this congress.

913
00:50:38,911 --> 00:50:41,956
Yes, of course. Now it's spirit.

914
00:50:42,040 --> 00:50:44,042
Well, why didn't I think of that?

915
00:50:44,125 --> 00:50:48,254
No army, no Navy, no arms, no ammunition,

916
00:50:48,338 --> 00:50:52,634
no treasury, no friends,

917
00:50:52,717 --> 00:50:55,803
but, bless our soul, spirit.

918
00:50:56,804 --> 00:50:59,223
Mr. Lee, Mr. Hopkins,

919
00:50:59,307 --> 00:51:01,726
Mr. Rodney, colonel mckean,

920
00:51:01,809 --> 00:51:03,311
Dr. Franklin.

921
00:51:04,604 --> 00:51:08,900
Why have you joined
this incendiary little man,

922
00:51:09,651 --> 00:51:11,736
this Boston radical,

923
00:51:13,029 --> 00:51:14,530
this agitator,

924
00:51:15,907 --> 00:51:17,450
this demagogue,

925
00:51:17,950 --> 00:51:19,619
this madman?

926
00:51:19,702 --> 00:51:22,205
Are you calling me a madman, you...

927
00:51:23,456 --> 00:51:24,874
You fribble!

928
00:51:27,043 --> 00:51:29,962
You and your Pennsylvania proprietors,

929
00:51:30,046 --> 00:51:33,007
you cool, considerate men,

930
00:51:33,091 --> 00:51:35,259
you hang to the rear on every issue,

931
00:51:35,343 --> 00:51:38,721
so that if we should go under,
you'll still remain afloat.

932
00:51:38,805 --> 00:51:40,640
Are you calling me a coward?

933
00:51:41,307 --> 00:51:42,975
Yes. Coward!

934
00:51:43,685 --> 00:51:44,727
Madman!

935
00:51:44,811 --> 00:51:45,895
Landlord!

936
00:51:45,978 --> 00:51:47,230
Lawyer!

937
00:51:53,695 --> 00:51:55,655
Stop it! Stop it!

938
00:51:57,448 --> 00:52:00,743
This is the congress. Stop it, I say!

939
00:52:00,827 --> 00:52:02,078
The enemy's out there.

940
00:52:02,161 --> 00:52:03,830
No, Mr. Rodney, the enemy is here.

941
00:52:03,913 --> 00:52:06,749
No. I say he's out there.

942
00:52:06,833 --> 00:52:08,459
England.

943
00:52:08,543 --> 00:52:12,046
England closing in, cutting off our air.

944
00:52:12,130 --> 00:52:13,715
There's no time!

945
00:52:17,301 --> 00:52:18,511
No air.

946
00:52:19,846 --> 00:52:21,139
Dr. hall.

947
00:52:25,226 --> 00:52:26,728
Colonel mckean.

948
00:52:26,811 --> 00:52:28,604
Aye. It's the cancer.

949
00:52:29,731 --> 00:52:31,607
But he should go home.

950
00:52:32,608 --> 00:52:35,820
A man should die in his own bed.

951
00:52:37,488 --> 00:52:39,699
John. John Adams.

952
00:52:39,782 --> 00:52:41,409
I'm here, Caesar.

953
00:52:44,203 --> 00:52:46,289
I leave you

954
00:52:46,372 --> 00:52:48,666
a divided Delaware.

955
00:52:49,917 --> 00:52:51,294
Forgive me.

956
00:52:52,003 --> 00:52:54,088
I'll take you home, Caesar.

957
00:53:18,905 --> 00:53:21,115
I'll be back within the week.

958
00:53:28,706 --> 00:53:32,126
Mr. president,
south Carolina calls the question.

959
00:53:34,170 --> 00:53:35,379
What's that, Mr. Rutledge?

960
00:53:36,589 --> 00:53:38,633
I said, Mr. president,

961
00:53:38,716 --> 00:53:42,136
south Carolina desires to end the debate

962
00:53:43,763 --> 00:53:46,182
and calls the question of independence.

963
00:53:46,265 --> 00:53:48,476
- Delaware seconds.
- Thank you.

964
00:53:49,936 --> 00:53:52,980
Gentlemen, please!

965
00:53:53,064 --> 00:53:55,900
The question has been called and seconded.

966
00:53:56,984 --> 00:53:59,028
The secretary will record the vote.

967
00:53:59,111 --> 00:54:01,447
Franklin, do something. Think.

968
00:54:01,531 --> 00:54:03,533
I'm thinking, but nothing's coming.

969
00:54:03,616 --> 00:54:05,743
All those in favor
of the resolution on independence

970
00:54:05,827 --> 00:54:08,371
as proposed by the colony of Virginia,
signify by saying...

971
00:54:08,454 --> 00:54:09,956
Mr. secretary.

972
00:54:10,748 --> 00:54:12,708
Will you please read the resolution again?

973
00:54:12,792 --> 00:54:13,918
What?

974
00:54:15,127 --> 00:54:16,295
I've forgotten it.

975
00:54:16,379 --> 00:54:17,964
Now, Benjamin...

976
00:54:20,466 --> 00:54:23,177
"Resolved, that these united colonies are,

977
00:54:23,261 --> 00:54:25,888
"and of a right ought to be,
free and independent..."

978
00:54:32,270 --> 00:54:35,857
Excuse me.
Ls this the continental congress?

979
00:54:35,940 --> 00:54:38,526
Yes, I can see that it must be.

980
00:54:39,735 --> 00:54:41,863
It's all right. We found it.

981
00:54:42,363 --> 00:54:44,740
We've been looking
for you everywhere, you see.

982
00:54:44,824 --> 00:54:47,451
Someone told us
that you might be at carpenters' hall

983
